<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
pre {
  display: block;
  font-family: monospace;
  white-space: pre;
  margin: 1em 0;
} 
.line{
	counter-increment: linenumber;
}
.line:before{
	content: counter(linenumber);
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<p>A pre element is displayed like this:</p>

<pre>
	<div class='line'>Text in a pre element</div>
	<div class='line'>is displayed in a fixed-width</div>
	<div class='line'>font, and it preserves</div>
	<div class='line'>both      spaces and</div>
	<div class='line'>line breaks</div>
</pre>

<p>Change the default CSS settings to see the effect.</p>

</body>
